            <entry xml:id="entry_app" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>app</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>appæ</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>ядро</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>kernel</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>косточка</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>stone</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сердцевина</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>core</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>содержание</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>contents</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Из <mentioned xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>ḥabb</w>
                        <gloss><q>зерно</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                        extralang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>косточка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>heb</w>
                        <gloss><q>зерно</q></gloss></mentioned>; отпадение в осетинском начального
                    %iḥ%i, как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aʒatxana"/> (тюркское посредство?).
                    Наряду с %iapp%i имеем <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qapp"/> ‘ядро’,
                    ‘testiculum’; если рассматривать %iapp%i и %iqapp%i как два варианта одного и
                    того же слова, то для передачи арабского начального %iḥ%i через %iq%i трудно
                    было бы подыскать еще один пример; не произошла ли в %iqapp%i контаминация с
                    другим %bарабским%b словом <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/>
                        <w>qalb</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>qalb</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>qalp</w>
                        <gloss><q>сердце</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>сердцевина</q></gloss></mentioned>?</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">From <mentioned xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>ḥabb</w>
                        <gloss><q>grain</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                        extralang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>stone</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>heb</w>
                        <gloss><q>grain</q></gloss></mentioned>; the fall of the initial %iḥ%i in
                    Ossetic is as in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aʒatxana"/> (via Turkic?).
                    Alongside with %iapp%i there is <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qapp"/> ‘kernel’,
                    ‘testiculum’; if %iapp%i and %iqapp%i are considered as two variants of the same
                    word, then it would be difficult to find another example on the expression of
                    the initial Arabic %iḥ%i via %iq%i; is not in %iqapp%i a contamination with
                    another %bArabic%b word <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/>
                        <w>qalb</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>qalb</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>qalp</w>
                        <gloss><q>heart</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>core</q></gloss></mentioned>?</etym>
            </entry>
